eports indicate that TiVo is mostly manually tagging popular TV shows with markers that are downloaded to the Bolt. New solution to an old problem. For example, Engadget reports
"TiVo is managing this by basically having people watch the programs on\xc2\xa0 certain networks (the top 20 or so most popular, between 4PM and\xc2\xa0 midnight) and mark where the actual show begins and the commercials end.\xc2\xa0 Your Bolt downloads the information, and is ready for skipping at will\xc2\xa0 shortly after the shows are recorded. You'll know which shows have\xc2\xa0 commercials that can be skipped, because they've got a big green skip\xc2\xa0 button in the guide now. "
